The leopard seal was found ashore on Milnerton Beach in Cape Town. JOHANNESBURG - Cape Town beachgoers have been cautioned not to go near a leopard seal which was spotted ashore near Milnerton. A section of the beach was cordoned off on Wednesday in the interest of public safety after the leopard seal was spotted. The City of Cape Town's Gregg Oelofse said on Thursday that the leopard seal had managed to move. READ: Lion cub rescued in Cape Town suburb "We are not sure where it is at the moment because it has moved. Efforts are being made to ensure that we find it but we do suspect that it has moved off on its own," said Oelofse. He said beachgoers need to ensure that they exercise caution should they come across the leopard seal. The leopard seal is a predator and should be considered dangerous.